INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the Civil Service Law to allow candidates for employment who are veterans to use military credit points multiple times on more than one eligible list.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Civil Service Law to allow candidates for employment who are veterans to use military credit points multiple times on more than one eligible list.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to façade inspections and air conditioners.
EventItemMatterName: Façade inspections and air conditioners.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the U.S. Congress to pass H.R. 2236, also known as the Breastfeeding Promotion Act of 2007.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass H.R. 2236, also known as the Breastfeeding Promotion Act of 2007.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York to preserve the existing Green Thumb Community Gardens and to set aside more parkland, open space and vacant lots to be developed as permanent Green Thumb Community Gardens.
EventItemMatterName: Preserve the existing Green Thumb Community Gardens.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Office of Court Administration to stop selling information from landlord/tenant proceedings in the Housing Part of the New York City Civil Court.
EventItemMatterName: Office of Court Administration to stop selling information from landlord/tenant proceedings in the Housing Part of the New York City Civil Court.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to eliminating professional certification of plans submitted to the department of buildings regarding curb cuts and requiring the notification of community boards and council members upon the receipt by the department of buildings of an application for a curb cut.
EventItemMatterName: Eliminating professional certification of plans submitted to the department of buildings regarding curb cuts and requiring the notification of community boards and council members.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the illegally created curb cuts to be restored, making those who maintain illegally created curb cuts liable for penalties, requiring the department of transportation to restore illegally created curb cuts and providing for the reimbursement to the department for the cost for such work.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the illegally created curb cuts to be restored, making those who maintain illegally created curb cuts liable for penalties.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.5948 to amend the private housing finance law, or in the alternative, to authorize the City to enact a local law that would provide tenants a right of first refusal in the event that their Mitchell-Lama or project-based Section 8 buildings are sold, in order to preserve affordable housing in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.5948 to amend the private housing finance law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to protection of trees during construction.
EventItemMatterName: Protection of trees during construction.
